1
00:00:00,553 --> 00:00:08,653
<i>Yeah, turn your sadness into kindness,</i>
<i>your uniqueness into strength</i>

2
00:00:08,828 --> 00:00:17,065
<i>Even if you get lost, let's start walking</i>

3
00:00:17,303 --> 00:00:19,294
<i>One more time</i>

4
00:00:22,308 --> 00:00:26,074
<i>Are you really happy</i>

5
00:00:26,146 --> 00:00:29,513
<i>when you're always meeting</i>
<i>to someone's expectations?</i>

6
00:00:29,716 --> 00:00:33,277
<i>Even if you change to</i>
<i>who you really wanna be</i>

7
00:00:33,653 --> 00:00:37,020
<i>Will you always have a great smile?</i>

8
00:00:37,090 --> 00:00:44,519
<i>Dreaming of only "the beginning,"</i>
<i>I wake up</i>

9
00:00:44,597 --> 00:00:53,733
<i>and someday, I'll live on my own.</i>

10
00:00:53,807 --> 00:01:01,839
<i>Yes, precious things are never in shape</i>

11
00:01:02,081 --> 00:01:08,919
<i>You never know what it is</i>
<i>when you get it or lose it</i>

12
00:01:08,988 --> 00:01:17,054
<i>Yeah, turn your sadness into kindness,</i>
<i>your uniqueness into strength</i>

13
00:01:17,363 --> 00:01:25,828
<i>Even if you get lost,</i>
<i>let's start walking</i>

14
00:01:25,905 --> 00:01:27,930
<i>One more time</i>

15
00:01:38,963 --> 00:01:44,799
<i>Assassin of the Moonlit Night</i>

16
00:01:54,245 --> 00:01:56,406
<i>T-This guy...</i>

17
00:02:01,952 --> 00:02:02,816
Sasuke!

18
00:02:05,222 --> 00:02:06,746
<i>So we were too late...</i>

19
00:02:11,428 --> 00:02:12,360
Those guys...

20
00:02:21,138 --> 00:02:23,231
Sa... Sakura...?

21
00:02:27,945 --> 00:02:29,310
You guys...

22
00:02:29,713 --> 00:02:30,543
<i>T-This...</i>

23
00:02:31,482 --> 00:02:33,313
<i>He probably fought recklessly...</i>

24
00:02:34,985 --> 00:02:36,213
<i>like that time!</i>

25
00:02:39,623 --> 00:02:40,521
Sasuke!

26
00:02:41,158 --> 00:02:44,719
<i>Kakashi Sensei said there was nothing</i>
<i>to worry about with the bruise!</i>

27
00:02:44,862 --> 00:02:47,092
So tell me... Sakura...

28
00:02:48,165 --> 00:02:49,132
Sakura!

29
00:02:50,034 --> 00:02:50,932
What do you want?!

30
00:02:52,236 --> 00:02:54,727
This guy... Who is he?!

31
00:02:55,806 --> 00:02:58,274
His outward appearance
is different, but...

32
00:02:59,510 --> 00:03:01,444
he's that guy called Gaara.

33
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:07,510
<i>When I came into this world, I took the life</i>
<i>of the woman some might call my mother.</i>

34
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:10,514
<i>So that I could become</i>
<i>the strongest Shinobi...</i>

35
00:03:10,588 --> 00:03:13,182
<i>my father brought his Ninjutsu upon me,</i>

36
00:03:13,257 --> 00:03:15,452
<i>and so I became possessed</i>
<i>by a Sand Spirit.</i>

37
00:03:16,427 --> 00:03:18,987
<i>I was born a monster.</i>

38
00:03:20,631 --> 00:03:23,065
<i>So that's what he was saying...</i>

39
00:03:23,634 --> 00:03:26,125
<i>He's the one who hurt Sasuke...</i>

40
00:03:26,303 --> 00:03:27,565
Hey young girl!

41
00:03:28,472 --> 00:03:31,669
I want you to know that
I'm not the fighting type!

42
00:03:31,809 --> 00:03:33,470
I can see that by looking at you!

43
00:03:35,946 --> 00:03:37,811
<i>In any case,</i>
<i>I need to get away from here</i>

44
00:03:37,882 --> 00:03:41,318
<i>and somehow take Sasuke to</i>
<i>where Kakashi Sensei is!</i>

45
00:03:44,622 --> 00:03:45,816
You...

46
00:03:48,525 --> 00:03:49,457
Sasuke...!

47
00:03:50,094 --> 00:03:52,688
<i>Well! Your limit is two shots...</i>

48
00:03:53,931 --> 00:03:55,091
That's about it...

49
00:03:56,300 --> 00:04:00,566
The third shot won't be activated...
Remember this well.

50
00:04:02,306 --> 00:04:04,570
If you try to force a Jutsu to activate...

51
00:04:04,642 --> 00:04:07,110
not only will the Jutsu
not properly activate,

52
00:04:07,177 --> 00:04:09,202
but your Chakra will deplete to zero...

53
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:12,174
and in the worst case, you'll die!

54
00:04:18,489 --> 00:04:24,052
Even if you were to survive,
absolutely nothing good will come of it.

55
00:04:25,496 --> 00:04:27,157
Especially in your case...

56
00:04:28,532 --> 00:04:29,590
Is it the Curse Mark...?

57
00:04:35,205 --> 00:04:36,832
If you let your hatred take over you,

58
00:04:36,907 --> 00:04:39,239
and rely on the power
of the Curse Mark...

59
00:04:39,743 --> 00:04:42,109
your development will stop there.

60
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:46,272
If that happens, you won't
be able to beat Itachi.

61
00:04:48,485 --> 00:04:51,249
<i>In any case,</i>
<i>I need to get control over this.</i>

62
00:04:53,657 --> 00:04:54,681
Sasuke!

63
00:04:55,859 --> 00:04:57,724
I see you're...

64
00:04:58,963 --> 00:05:01,261
the one I failed to kill that time.

65
00:05:03,033 --> 00:05:07,299
<i>I live fighting for only myself</i>
<i>and loving myself...</i>

66
00:05:07,771 --> 00:05:10,934
<i>And as long as there are others to kill...</i>

67
00:05:11,008 --> 00:05:13,340
<i>I will never disappear.</i>

68
00:05:15,512 --> 00:05:18,811
L-Let's run! Everyone!

69
00:05:32,529 --> 00:05:34,497
Die! Sasuke Uchiha!

70
00:05:39,036 --> 00:05:40,230
Sakura!

71
00:05:51,749 --> 00:05:53,114
Out of the way!

72
00:06:09,633 --> 00:06:10,725
Sakura!

73
00:06:14,471 --> 00:06:16,996
How could she stand
in the way of that Gaara...?

74
00:06:18,008 --> 00:06:23,105
Darn! Darn!
What the heck should we do?!

75
00:06:26,884 --> 00:06:28,374
<i>Just with him, I don't want to...</i>

76
00:06:29,486 --> 00:06:31,477
<i>Now, let me feel it!</i>

77
00:06:41,231 --> 00:06:42,220
Why...?

78
00:06:50,207 --> 00:06:52,300
<i>Gaara, Please calm down.</i>

79
00:07:08,358 --> 00:07:09,825
It's no use after all...

80
00:07:10,894 --> 00:07:12,418
The sand gets in the way.

81
00:07:13,997 --> 00:07:15,157
Gaara...

82
00:07:16,366 --> 00:07:17,390
Yashamaru!

83
00:07:18,635 --> 00:07:20,330
I may not look it,

84
00:07:20,404 --> 00:07:23,237
but Lord Kazekage charged me
to look after your physical condition

85
00:07:23,307 --> 00:07:25,741
as a member of medical corps
and to be with you.

86
00:07:26,443 --> 00:07:29,276
Please do not do such things
in front of me.

87
00:07:31,782 --> 00:07:34,979
Although the sand will protect you...

88
00:07:38,322 --> 00:07:40,756
Yashamaru... I'm sorry...

89
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:45,720
Oh, this.? It's just a scrape.

90
00:07:48,665 --> 00:07:49,825
A scrape...

91
00:07:51,034 --> 00:07:52,023
Is it painful?

92
00:07:54,238 --> 00:07:57,605
A little bit... But it'll heal in no time.

93
00:08:06,450 --> 00:08:07,815
Hey Yashamaru...

94
00:08:07,951 --> 00:08:09,077
What is it?

95
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:11,447
What is pain?

96
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:18,860
I've... never once had a wound so...

97
00:08:19,129 --> 00:08:21,063
I wondered what it's like...

98
00:08:22,432 --> 00:08:23,831
Well...

99
00:08:24,368 --> 00:08:26,427
How can I explain it?

100
00:08:27,604 --> 00:08:30,505
It's like it's distressing, or difficult...

101
00:08:31,742 --> 00:08:34,302
In other words, to be hit or cut...

102
00:08:34,545 --> 00:08:38,572
Maybe I should say it's a feeling
of not being able to bear it,

103
00:08:38,649 --> 00:08:40,378
of not being able to stay normal...

104
00:08:41,652 --> 00:08:43,210
I can't say it well,

105
00:08:43,287 --> 00:08:46,688
but I suppose it means a situation
that's not very good.

106
00:08:59,036 --> 00:09:00,469
Yashamaru...

107
00:09:00,537 --> 00:09:01,504
Yes?

108
00:09:02,472 --> 00:09:08,069
So, do you dislike me... Yashamaru?

109
00:09:19,890 --> 00:09:24,088
People live their lives while
hurting others and while being hurt.

110
00:09:24,728 --> 00:09:28,357
But it's not so easy for
people to dislike others.

111
00:09:31,501 --> 00:09:33,560
Thank you, Yashamaru.

112
00:09:34,438 --> 00:09:37,407
I think I sort of understand
what pain is now.

113
00:09:37,941 --> 00:09:38,873
I see...

114
00:09:41,345 --> 00:09:46,214
So... maybe I'm injured too?
The same as everyone?

115
00:09:47,384 --> 00:09:49,443
I'm always... in pain.

116
00:09:50,854 --> 00:09:52,515
I'm not bleeding, but...

117
00:09:52,589 --> 00:09:55,353
I've been having a lot of
pain around... here.

118
00:10:17,781 --> 00:10:20,841
Blood does flow from a wound
on the body

119
00:10:20,917 --> 00:10:22,714
and the wound may appear painful.

120
00:10:23,053 --> 00:10:26,420
But as time passes, the pain
naturally disappears.

121
00:10:26,723 --> 00:10:29,191
By using medicine,
the healing is even faster.

122
00:10:30,761 --> 00:10:33,491
But what's dangerous is
a wound of the heart.

123
00:10:33,764 --> 00:10:36,232
Nothing has more trouble healing

124
00:10:37,367 --> 00:10:38,629
A wound of the heart?

125
00:10:39,002 --> 00:10:42,199
A wound on the body and
a wound of the heart are slightly different.

126
00:10:43,106 --> 00:10:46,473
Unlike a wound on the body,
there is no ointment and sometimes,

127
00:10:46,543 --> 00:10:48,636
it doesn't heal for one's entire life.

128
00:10:55,986 --> 00:10:59,581
But there is one thing that
can cure a wound of the heart.

129
00:11:01,525 --> 00:11:03,891
However, this is a complicated medicine.

130
00:11:04,127 --> 00:11:06,618
It can only be given to you
by another person.

131
00:11:06,763 --> 00:11:09,061
What? What must I do to...?

132
00:11:10,167 --> 00:11:12,431
The thing that can cure
a wound of the heart.

133
00:11:13,170 --> 00:11:14,194
That is...

134
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:18,437
Iove.

135
00:11:19,109 --> 00:11:20,406
Love?

136
00:11:20,711 --> 00:11:21,541
Yes.

137
00:11:21,712 --> 00:11:26,376
H-How can I get it?
What do I need to do for this pain to be...?

138
00:11:26,950 --> 00:11:30,317
It has already been given to you, Gaara.

139
00:11:30,654 --> 00:11:31,552
Huh?

140
00:11:35,459 --> 00:11:40,158
Love is... a heart that desires to serve
a precious person who is close to oneself,

141
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:44,792
to love and watch over that person,
just like my older sister did.

142
00:11:45,535 --> 00:11:49,232
I believe that my older sister
loved you, Gaara.

143
00:11:50,540 --> 00:11:54,874
Sand Spirit Shukaku is a spirit of a living
person used for the purpose of attacks.

144
00:11:55,746 --> 00:12:00,843
The sand which automatically tries to
protect you is like the love of a mother.

145
00:12:01,818 --> 00:12:06,221
I believe that sand is filled
with your mother's will.

146
00:12:08,024 --> 00:12:13,587
My sister... probably wanted to
protect you even more after dying...

147
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,061
Yashamaru...

148
00:12:18,902 --> 00:12:19,926
What is it?

149
00:12:20,937 --> 00:12:24,998
Thanks for what you did earlier...
for stopping me.

150
00:12:25,776 --> 00:12:27,141
You are welcome.

151
00:12:28,445 --> 00:12:32,506
You are a precious person
who is near me, Gaara!

152
00:12:55,839 --> 00:12:59,570
Can you understand... my pain?

153
00:13:09,052 --> 00:13:10,713
It tastes like iron...

154
00:14:24,494 --> 00:14:25,426
Twenty!

155
00:14:32,636 --> 00:14:34,365
Twenty one!

156
00:14:48,885 --> 00:14:52,343
Leaf... Hurricane!

157
00:14:55,725 --> 00:14:57,818
How many did you take
down Kakashi?

158
00:14:58,161 --> 00:14:59,287
Twenty two.

159
00:15:00,430 --> 00:15:02,955
Huh, it seems I win again!

160
00:15:05,101 --> 00:15:07,569
That was my twenty third.

161
00:15:07,637 --> 00:15:09,229
Yeah, yeah all right...

162
00:15:10,006 --> 00:15:12,873
That poser attitude of yours
still makes you cool!

163
00:15:12,943 --> 00:15:14,808
That's the reason you are my rival!

164
00:15:15,946 --> 00:15:17,436
- Let's go!
- All right!

165
00:15:33,763 --> 00:15:37,062
Hey, Yashamaru...
I have a favor to ask!

166
00:15:37,901 --> 00:15:38,833
What is it?

167
00:15:40,403 --> 00:15:41,961
I want some ointment.

168
00:15:51,915 --> 00:15:54,907
Sorry about earlier...
It must've hurt.

169
00:15:55,518 --> 00:15:57,611
This is medicine.

170
00:15:58,021 --> 00:15:58,885
If you want it

171
00:15:58,955 --> 00:16:00,946
Go home... freak!

172
00:16:31,721 --> 00:16:33,484
Oh, what the?!

173
00:16:33,556 --> 00:16:35,490
Hey, be careful, you brat...

174
00:16:35,992 --> 00:16:37,823
Y-You are...

175
00:16:40,296 --> 00:16:42,560
- <i>Again...</i>
- <i>Go home, freak!</i>

176
00:16:43,166 --> 00:16:44,030
<i>These eyes...</i>

177
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,965
<i>Y-You are...</i>

178
00:16:46,169 --> 00:16:48,399
<i>Why...? Why?!</i>

179
00:16:49,205 --> 00:16:50,866
H-Hey!

180
00:16:57,380 --> 00:16:58,847
What the? What's going on?

181
00:16:58,915 --> 00:17:00,109
It's... it's Gaara!

182
00:17:00,183 --> 00:17:02,481
Hey! This guy's dead.

183
00:17:18,735 --> 00:17:19,929
<i>Father...</i>

184
00:17:33,283 --> 00:17:36,309
<i>As I thought... Things don't go well...</i>

185
00:17:40,290 --> 00:17:43,726
<i>Why is it...that only I'm such a freak?!</i>

186
00:17:45,462 --> 00:17:47,987
<i>What...am I?!</i>

187
00:17:49,232 --> 00:17:52,895
<i>The thing that can cure</i>
<i>a wound of the heart is love.</i>

188
00:17:54,404 --> 00:17:55,803
<i>Yashamaru!</i>

189
00:18:15,425 --> 00:18:16,357
<i>Huh?</i>

190
00:18:20,563 --> 00:18:23,464
<i>Why? Why me...?</i>

191
00:18:24,067 --> 00:18:25,659
<i>Why always me?!</i>

192
00:18:51,494 --> 00:18:54,554
Who...? Why...?

193
00:19:30,733 --> 00:19:33,827
Well done... Gaara.

194
00:19:41,744 --> 00:19:43,336
Yashamaru...!

195
00:19:55,058 --> 00:19:56,218
<i>It's those eyes...</i>

196
00:19:59,495 --> 00:20:03,158
What's the matter?
Weren't you gonna run away?

197
00:20:05,368 --> 00:20:06,460
Sasuke...

198
00:20:08,605 --> 00:20:09,697
Naruto...

199
00:20:13,610 --> 00:20:19,344
What are these two... to you?!

200
00:20:20,917 --> 00:20:26,321
T-These two are... my friends!

201
00:20:26,823 --> 00:20:29,724
Try laying so much as
another finger on them!

202
00:20:30,093 --> 00:20:32,357
I'll clobber you!

203
00:20:40,637 --> 00:20:44,664
So... what's the matter?!
Weren't you gonna clobber me?

204
00:20:47,844 --> 00:20:49,004
Hurry up and come at me...

205
00:20:56,052 --> 00:20:58,282
Darn it!

206
00:21:05,862 --> 00:21:15,931
<i>Everyone makes mistakes</i>
<i>It's nothing to be ashamed about</i>

207
00:21:16,372 --> 00:21:27,215
<i>Don't let this scar be for naught</i>
<i>Walk with a smile</i>

208
00:21:37,327 --> 00:21:42,959
<i>Yes, breathe in the air</i>
<i>Lift your face to the sky and jump</i>

209
00:21:43,032 --> 00:21:47,992
<i>If it rains, take a break</i>
<i>Go where the wind takes you</i>

210
00:21:48,371 --> 00:21:53,274
<i>So many regrets</i>
<i>Don't let this scar be for naught</i>

211
00:21:53,343 --> 00:21:58,474
<i>Let's go carve the badges in our chest</i>
<i>Yes, it's Show Time, life begins now.</i>

212
00:21:58,548 --> 00:22:08,719
<i>Everyone makes mistakes</i>
<i>It's nothing to be ashamed about</i>

213
00:22:09,025 --> 00:22:19,458
<i>Don't let this scar be for naught</i>
<i>Walk with a smile</i>

214
00:22:19,535 --> 00:22:30,104
<i>Transform sadness into the wind</i>
<i>and continue to forge on</i>

215
00:22:30,179 --> 00:22:35,742
<i>Forge on strong</i>

216
00:22:47,697 --> 00:22:49,995
I know this guy's strength.

217
00:22:50,233 --> 00:22:55,102
I may seem like a senseless
weakling to him.

218
00:22:55,905 --> 00:23:00,774
But... what's?
What's this feeling welling up inside me?

219
00:23:01,311 --> 00:23:02,505
I don't know...

220
00:23:02,579 --> 00:23:09,109
I don't know,
but I just don't want to lose to this guy!

221
00:23:09,919 --> 00:23:13,480
Next time: "Light vs. Dark:
The Two Faces of Gaara"
